<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Bear Counter</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">The Bear Counter can be used to introduce various mathematics concept.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Drag any bears<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/icon_bearcounter.png" style="vertical-align:middle">in the grids and get the children to count them. The bear counters can be used to demonstrate addition and subtraction. Use two bears of different colours for addition and use only one colour for subtraction. It can also be used for comparison (more and less), making pattern, data sorting and graphing too.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">You may take away by discarding (double-click) or crossing out by using the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_pencil.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button. Use the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_eraser.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">or<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_clear.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button to remove all the scribbles with the pencil tool. To start counting a new set of numbers with the bear counters, click the<img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_reset.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle">button.</p>
</div>